subject: Live Concert; audience;
source: Sen 421's > patched thru 3(?) decks > Toshiba KT-R2 Walkman > MAC (Sony UCX-S) > Sony TC-D5M > Soundblaster > Soundforge > CD-Wave > FLAC
notes: People were taping very stealthily. I couldn't find anyone to patch out of before the show started, so I didn't tape the first set. During the break, I located some tapers in the center of the main floor, aprx 15th row or thereabouts, who agreed to patch me in at the end of their line of decks. They kept their mics pretty low, aprx 5-1/2 to 6 feet high. The very beginning of Uncle John's Band is missing and fades in (sorry!). There were little cuts and level changes during the drums where the other tapes were flipped. I repaired those with Soundforge.
